(phrasal verb) (back up|back sth <-> up) = to move backwards especially in a vehicle, (back sb/sth <-> up) {B2} = to support sb/sth or to say that what sb say/ etc. is true; (back sth <-> up) {C1} {computers} = to prepare a second copy of a file/program/etc. that can be used if the main one fails or needs extra support